know that we have a crush on them?

290
00:23:33,520 --> 00:23:34,710
This is hard.

291
00:23:36,280 --> 00:23:39,050
I would just tell them directly.

292
00:23:40,180 --> 00:23:44,910
If not, I'll do everything
to let them know that I have a crush on them.

293
00:23:47,920 --> 00:23:52,550
What if you knew that they didn't like you?

294
00:23:53,520 --> 00:23:55,280
Have you already asked that person

295
00:23:56,000 --> 00:23:57,490
to make you think like that?

296
00:23:59,560 --> 00:24:01,840
Maybe it's just because

297
00:24:01,880 --> 00:24:07,160
they don’t know yet.

298
00:24:09,320 --> 00:24:12,940
If I were to say something to you,

299
00:24:14,240 --> 00:24:16,180
could you keep it a secret?

300
00:24:16,680 --> 00:24:18,120
Sure. What is it?

301
00:24:19,920 --> 00:24:21,250
I have a crush on Phra Aek.

302
00:24:26,440 --> 00:24:27,190
Oh...

303
00:24:27,800 --> 00:24:29,140
Someone dropped more trash.

304
00:24:37,160 --> 00:24:38,540
Thanks, Noey.

305
00:24:40,560 --> 00:24:43,750
I will not tell anyone about it.

306
00:24:44,240 --> 00:24:45,230
I promise.

307
00:24:46,120 --> 00:24:47,120
Really?

308
00:24:48,800 --> 00:24:49,670
Mm.

309
00:24:50,120 --> 00:24:53,720
I will also help bring you
and Phra Aek together

310
00:24:53,760 --> 00:24:55,050
in return.

311
00:25:10,560 --> 00:25:12,110
Just pick up the phone first if you need to.

312
00:25:15,320 --> 00:25:16,320
It's fine.

313
00:25:16,960 --> 00:25:18,680
Let's continue with the shoot.

314
00:25:19,240 --> 00:25:20,030
Let's go.

315
00:25:32,520 --> 00:25:37,720
Alright, these are photos,
with the trash bin and garbage as the subject.

316
00:25:37,760 --> 00:25:41,600
I shot them from the morning to noon, evening,

317
00:25:41,640 --> 00:25:43,600
and the morning of the next day.

318
00:25:44,520 --> 00:25:47,870
You can see that at each time of day,
piles of trash get bigger over time,

319
00:25:48,100 --> 00:25:50,310
which is probably how it normally is.

320
00:25:53,320 --> 00:25:54,160
Uh...

321
00:25:55,240 --> 00:25:56,110
The concept...

322
00:25:56,560 --> 00:25:57,320
The concept.

323
00:25:59,440 --> 00:26:01,310
By studying these pictures,

324
00:26:01,600 --> 00:26:07,000
it's clear that the garbage
we dispose of doesn't simply vanish.

325
00:26:07,280 --> 00:26:10,660
It remains and keeps growing in size.

326
00:26:11,400 --> 00:26:13,960
This issue needs to be resolved.

327
00:26:14,000 --> 00:26:15,400
It's not limited to urban areas,

328
00:26:15,510 --> 00:26:19,830
but smaller communities
and even individual homes.

329
00:26:20,500 --> 00:26:24,120
If we start with a small thing,
such as sorting the trash,

330
00:26:24,320 --> 00:26:27,090
we might be able to reduce the waste.

331
00:26:27,520 --> 00:26:29,360
Every neighborhood will become cleaner,

332
00:26:29,400 --> 00:26:31,540
improving the environment.

333
00:26:40,230 --> 00:26:41,320
That's great.

334
00:26:41,360 --> 00:26:42,280
It's phenomenal.

335
00:26:42,880 --> 00:26:45,660
I didn't expect to see
this style of photos from you.

336
00:26:46,760 --> 00:26:50,370
Focusing more on composition
and the trash bins

337
00:26:50,960 --> 00:26:53,330
could highlight the concept even better.

338
00:26:53,760 --> 00:26:54,480
Thank you.

339
00:26:54,520 --> 00:26:56,350
I will apply it to my future projects.

340
00:26:57,320 --> 00:27:00,800
Lastly, a big thank you goes to Nong Noey.

341
00:27:01,120 --> 00:27:06,640
He went to the shooting location with me
and gave me inspiration.

342
00:27:07,250 --> 00:27:08,980
Good job.

343
00:27:11,000 --> 00:27:11,720
Hey.

344
00:27:12,360 --> 00:27:15,070
I think he's taking my place for the project.

345
00:27:15,280 --> 00:27:16,520
How is he this talented?

346
00:27:18,760 --> 00:27:19,760
You bet he's good.

347
00:27:19,930 --> 00:27:21,560
I trained him myself.

348
